This paper discusses a new type of online fraud and provides a crime script analysis of the 'eWhoring' business model. The paper focuses on the use of various online services for carrying out this fraud type, including email, video, dating sites, social media, classified advertisements, and payment platforms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
